1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g3 {If you want the Catalan opening, you'd normally go 3. g3 , but with the insertion of 3. Nc3 and Bb4 , this instead becomes a Nimzo-Catalan hybrid. White hopes to see a magnificent bishop on g2 controlling the whole board, including the important e4 central square.} Bxc3+ {I'll admit this is a weird move, but hear me out: I'd like to compare this to the line with 4. a3 , where the positions after Bxc3 are considered nice for Black. 4. g3 didn't actually do much to help white's development. In the 4. a3 lines, white normally goes for a bishop placement on d3 to point towards h7 and Black's king.  Also, Bg5 is often a very annoying move to face for Black, but with the pawn on g3 this becomes impossible. Bg5 is met by h6 , when Bh4 is no longer a possibility on account of g5 trapping the bishop.  So the move g3 , while it might be considered a free move compared to a3 , is detrimental to White's position if you play the same plans as in 4. a3 . And I'm gonna prove that the plans unique to this move order aren't that impressive either.} (4... c5 {is a worthwhile alternative for Black, when} 5. Nf3 {is White's best option, transposing back to the 4. Nf3 -lines .}) 5. bxc3 d6 {As always when we take on c3 and give White doubled pawns, we're placing our pawns on dark squares to compensate for losing our dark-squared bishop.} 6. f3 {tries to build a big pawn center, just as in the 4. a3 lines.} c5 7. e4 Nc6 {Black puts immediate pressure on d4 , while white struggles to organize the pieces. One possible plan for white is to go all-in attacking with the pawns, but note how Black finds good squares for the pieces:} 8. h4 O-O 9. Kf2 b6 10. g4 Ba6 {The king found safety, knowing that pawns alone cannot checkmate it, while the c4 -pawn is a clear target.} 11. h5 {It's important to be weary of the Bg5 -pin, which hasn't really been an option earlier because Black could kick the bishop away with h6 .} Nd7 {takes care of the problem, and Black will follow up with Na5 next, likely winning a pawn.} *

