. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Bxf3 {Leaving White with a powerful bishop on f3 . In return, Black is able to snatch a pawn.} exd4 15. Bxc6 {avoids losing a pawn, but also gives up all the pressure. Black is equal...} bxc6 16. Qxd4 Rb6 {when Black is closer to controlling the open files than white. In fact it's White who has to be accurate.} 17. c5 Qxd4 18. cxd4 dxc5 19. dxc5 Rb5 {Black has the worse pawn structure, but better activity with the rook. The two cancel each other out and a draw is likely.} *

