$1 {The best way to deal with White's amazing diagonal for the g2 -bishop is to get a strong piece ourselves.} 16. axb3 Nd4 {Black's knight is very annoying, so white will likely eliminate it with} 17. e3 Nf3+ 18. Bxf3 Qxf3 19. O-O {= when the position is equal.}) 13. Bxe5 bxa2 14. Bxg7 Rd8 {The computer prefers Black, but this is an extremely dangerous position for both sides. It's important to note that Black is able to play Be6 soon, which will keep the vital a2 -pawn protected.} *

