night to d4 , and need to eliminate White's knight to make it happen.} 14. Qxb3 {This lets Black's pieces join the attack with threats.} Nd4 15. Qd1 Rc8 16. O-O {Finally white got the king to safety, but Black sits ready with the counterattack.} Rc2 17. e3 Ne2+ 18. Kh1 Qxd1 19. Raxd1 Rxb2 {Black is better with a pawn up, although a draw is still the most likely result.} *

