e white tries to delay e4 since it blocks White's bishop. There's also ideas of going aggressive with f4 , but Black stands fine...} Ng6 12. f4 {Black gets a very good position if you know your stuff.} Ng4 13. Nf3 f5 {Black is not interested in getting steamrolled on the kingside, and strikes out with f5 before white gets the opportunity to force Black back.} 14. h3 e4 {A counter in the center, and a sequence of exchanges ensues.} 15. hxg4 exd3 16. Qxd3 fxg4 17. Ng5 Qe8 {A very good placement for the queen to protect g6 and control the e-file.} 18. e4 h6 19. Ne6 Bxe6 20. dxe6 {Now, if Black couldn't take the pawn on e6 , this story would have a very different ending.} Qxe6 21. f5 Ne5 {Is an important saving resource, with a winning position.} *

