 Nf1 Nh5 {It's important to strike early, before White completes their plan.} 13. g3 {White needed to stop Nf4 , but now Black strikes.} f5 {We get all the pieces involved now, while breaking down White's dominant center.} 14. exf5 Nxf5 {Black has excellent piece activity. If white tries to punish the knights.} 15. g4 {Black starts an attack against White's king.} Nh4 16. gxh5 {White won the knight, but at what cost?} Ng2+ 17. Kd1 Bg4+ {All of Black's pieces get involved!} 18. Be2 Rxf2 {The rook as well!} 19. Bxg4 {White has to give away the queen to alleviate the pressure, but it won't stop Black from attacking anyway.} Rxc2 20. Kxc2 Qh4 {White got a lot of pieces for the queen, so materially it's fine. White's main problem is that Black still has good attacking chances.} *

