ith d5 and Bb5 +, which could cause some trouble.} 9. Be3 Nc6 {This is the key move! We're playing a pawn sacrifice.} 10. dxc5 {As we will see, this is actually a risky move. But it's definitely also the most testing one for Black's concept.} (10. O-O {gives Black very easy play after} cxd4 11. Nxd4 Bc5 {when White will have to trade away any hope of an advantage.}) 10... Ne5 11. Ba2 Nd3+ 12. Kf1 {It's a big concession for White to move the king, but White is hoping it doesn't matter in an endgame. However, Black doesn't have to acquiesce to White's plan.} b6 {This is the key move! Black has no intention to cashing in on the pawn just yet. Instead, the bishop gets a route to a6 , from where it will point down towards White's king.} (12... Bxc5 $2 13. Bxc5 Nxc5 14. e5 {would play straight into White's hands, when the uncastled White king would not be a major feature in the position as Black has no pieces in attacking positions.}) 13. cxb6 axb6 14. Rb1 {is the simple way of protecting the b2 -pawn.} Ba6 {Black continues the plan, but as does White.} 15. b4 {If White is allowed to play b5 , Black's counterplay may get shut down, so it's important to have a plan B. In Black's case: Getting the rook to the d-file.} Ra7 16. b5 Bb7 17. a4 {This is natural given the threat on a3 , but then Black strikes!} Bxe4 {Magnificent! Black is willing to give a full piece to get the rook involved quickly, and remove one of the few pawns defending White's king. White has a choice, but both are very scary.} 18. Nxe4 Nxe4 19. fxe4 Rd7 20. Ng1 {A clever move, intending Nf3 to give the king some protection along the f-file. But Black continues with admirable calm.} Bc5 {Stunning. Exchanging a key defender instead of rushing to make a discovered attack on White's queen.} 21. Bxc5 Nxc5 22. Qe1 g5 {Another amazing move, intending g4 to prevent the White knight from using the f3 -square.} 23. h3 Rd2 {White's bishop is stuck in the corner, severely lacking something to attack.} 24. Bd5 Rc2 {Computers say White can defend with perfect play, but I know I'd like my chances against any human.} *

