s to use pawns in an attempt to keep Black's bishop locked away on the queenside, but we're having none of it.} b5 {An absolutely necessary move. We need to weaken White's pawns to keep our bishop in play.} 11. Qc2 exd5 12. cxd5 Nxc3 13. Qxc3 {The main benefit of this move is that it prevents Black from playing b4 , which may leave the bishop on a6 out of play.} d6 14. Ng3 Nd7 {The knight is making its way to f6 , to put pressure on the d5 -pawn.} 15. Be2 Nf6 16. Qd2 Re8 17. O-O Rb8 {Black's big problem in this position is the bishop on a6 . Rb8 tries to help the bishop find a better position by taking over the defensive task of protecting the b5 -pawn. In a dream world Black would like to follow up with Bc8 and a5 , staking a claim to the queenside.} 18. b4 {White emphasises how much that a6 -bishop is not going to come to life on the queenside by blocking the b5 -pawn's future advance.} Bc8 {It's time to find greener pastures.} 19. Rfc1 Qb6 {The queen arrives to lend its support to Black's pawns. It also has the added benefit of making White's plan of central dominance with f3 and e4 more difficult to achieve, as the queen now points in towards White's king and the e3 -pawn.} 20. Bf3 {In general this is the right plan: the bishop must assist the e4 -pawn push. It's very important how the queenside hostilities are settled. Without the a-file opened yet, Black can stake a claim to it.} Bd7 21. e4 c4 {Releasing the tension is a strategically risky decision. If White can calmly maneuver the knight over to c3 , it would be putting pressure on the b5 -pawn while also blocking Black's passed pawn. But we are absolutely intending to cause trouble before White achieves that plan.} 22. Qf4 Ra8 {We go after the a-file and new tension there!} 23. Ne2 a5 24. Nc3 Ra6 {Being the one to decide when the a-file opens can be very advantageous! We prepare a doubling of the rooks before opening up, and even though White got a good knight on c3 , Black's control of what is about to be the only open file on the board holds more sway.} *

