ecause while it goes after White's knight, it also opens the diagonal down towards the rook in the corner.} 13. Bf3 {Trying to grab the rook is the only way to survive.} Nc6 {A shocker! Can't White just capture the knight?} 14. Nge2 {I feel like this is the kind of tricky move you can't find over the board -- you just have to know it. But if you knew this line, you'd never walk into it as White!} Qf6 {Black continues the all-out attack. This move forces White to find some very difficult defensive moves.} 15. exd4 cxd4 16. Nxd4 {White's greed is the only thing that can save them!} Nxd4 {A necessary sacrifice to keep the attack rolling.} 17. Bxa8 Ba6 {Black prevents castling and threatens Rxa8 as well as the surprising Ne2 !} 18. O-O-O {This gets the king to safety, and attacks the knight on d4 . The problem is that after} Ne2+ {The knight is saved. The king wasn't as safe as we initially thought. And the a8 -bishop is doomed. All in all a winning position for Black.} *

