Ng4 15. Qc2 {If White tries to escape, Black will paradoxically just retreat.} Nf6 {Once again leaving White with the question of how to avoid Ba6 .} 16. Rfe1 Ba6 17. Bf5 {sees White's bishop trying to get away, only to get struck...} Bc8 {when it's clear white won't be able to keep the bishop pair, leaving Black with a nice position.} *

