back with a good position, but I think this is the most straight-forward one.} 12. a4 {Tries to rush the bishop to a3 , but after some tactics Black is fine.} Na5 {In general this is an annoying move for White, as the c4 -bishop lacks a good square.} 13. Bd3 Nxc5 {Since we bothered White's bishop we get to take the pawn with a threat on the bishop.} 14. Ba3 Qxd3 15. Bxc5 Qxd1 16. Rfxd1 Re8 {Black is behind in development, but ahead on pawn structure. The two strategic elements will likely balance each other out to a draw.} *

