nd most recent attempt in this line. However, I'm not sure he's ever going back to this opening, as I think Black can just get the pieces out.} ({Once again there's no reason to fear} 11. dxc5 {as Black gets the pawn back with a good position after} Bxc3 12. bxc3 Qd5 {.}) 11... Qe7 {Once again I advocate simple development and avoiding cxd4 .} 12. Qe2 Rd8 13. Rd1 {This was played in Caruana-Dominguez.} Bd7 {When Black is moving the bishop out of the way, and getting the corner rook involved next. I think Black has a nice setup. White's c1 -bishop remains a problem.} *

