Nc5 {Black needed to get the remaining queenside pieces out, but it comes at the cost of ruining the kingside pawn structure.} 17. Bxf6 gxf6 {Despite being down a pawn, Black is better. Much thanks to the powerful knight on c5 . White is unable to exploit the broken pawns in front of Black's king, as there are issues with White's king position that take precedence. Black's queen is ready to cause some problems from the a5 -square.} *

