1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. e3 {White keeps the c4 -pawn protected while avoiding the forcing lines starting with cxd5 or a3 . It is not as innocent as it looks though.   In fact there are lots of tricky move orders to try to lure us away from our repertoire scheme, but I think the immediate strike in the center keeps us within our preferred setups.} c5 {Creating the early central tension is the best way to put pressure on White.} 6. dxc5 Ne4 {This is an extremely rare move, but I think it's a clever one. Black tries to create trouble for White's pawn structure.} ({If Black plays traditionally with} 6... Bxc5 {It's White who gets the advantage of the superior pawn structure after} 7. cxd5 exd5 8. Nf3 O-O 9. Be2 Nc6 10. O-O {White is ready to go Rd1 next and put pressure on Black's lone pawn in the center. Objectively it's okay for Black because of their active pieces, but I prefer to avoid such permanent pawn weaknesses.}) 7. Nf3 {To me this is a shocking move, as it does nothing to address the threats Black have created against c3 -- yet it is White's best move. Sometimes you just have to get the pieces out quickly. It's based on an important trick though, to avoid doubled c-pawns.} (7. Bd2 {causes no troubles as Black gets a pleasant position with the bishop pair after} Nxd2 8. Qxd2 dxc4 {.}) 7... Nxc3 {Giving White doubled pawns was our main plan, so we follow through on the threat.} 8. bxc3 {Initially the engine Stockfish is a big fan of this for White, but I find it hard to believe White can be better with a broken queenside structure.} Bxc5 9. cxd5 Qxd5 10. Bd3 {White pins their hopes on pressure towards the kingside, but some accurate defensive moves will deal with that.} Nd7 ({We should avoid} 10... Qh5 $6 {at this moment, as White can create trouble for the queen with} 11. h3 {when} O-O {?} 12. g4 {sees White cooking up some serious threats.}) 11. O-O Qh5 {After castling there's no need to fear the h3+g4 plan, so now the queen finds a safe haven here while defending the h7 -pawn, which will enable Black to castle next with a fine position.} *

