1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. a3 {White immediately grabs the bishop pair, but at the cost of having to move the queen around.} Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 Ne4 {I like this move, trying to punish White's lack of development by immediately going after the queen.} 7. Qc2 c5 {We're eager to blast open the center and start an attack while White's king is still stuck in the middle.} 8. dxc5 Nc6 {Black's intention was not to recapture the pawn on c5 . We're all about getting the pieces involved quickly and creating an attack on White's king.} 9. Nf3 {White calmly develops, but this doesn't cause any problems for Black as we try to regain the pawn on c5 with the queen.} Qa5+ ({With the knight on c6 , this check is now available because b4 will be met by ...Nxb4: b4??} 9... Nb4) 10. Nd2 {This move prevents Black's main plan of Qxc5 , but it allows black to continue moving the pieces into attacking positions. The position quickly becomes very dangerous for White.} Nd4 11. Qd3 {The queen is move exposed on d3 than d1 , but the threat on the d4 -knight gives White some extra time to figure out a defensive plan.} e5 {Protecting the knight and getting ready for Bf5 .} 12. b4 Qa4 {The threat of Nc2 means White still can't develop the kingside.} 13. Ra2 Nxd2 {After studying the alternative 13... Bf5 , I've concluded this is the most straightforward line for Black. The queen has to recapture to avoid getting hit by Bf5 next.} 14. Qxd2 a5 {Timing is everything and a5 is very well-timed here. We're trying to involve the a8 -rook without ever moving it.} 15. cxd5 (15. e3 {becomes the same thing as 15. cxd5 after} Nb3 16. Qc2 axb4 17. cxd5 {.}) 15... axb4 16. e4 {Letting the knight live on d4 is ill-advised. Black gets promising chances.} f5 {White's position is still under pressure, and the d4 -knight is troubling to deal with.} 17. Bd3 fxe4 18. Bxe4 {White would be much better if they could get the king to safety, but we won't allow it.} b3 19. Rb2 Qc4 {We prevent castling while simultaneously looking at the c5 - and d5 -pawns. Black has a solid advantage.} *

