nding the g7 -pawn. Instead it's important to start the counter-attack.} 19. Rxg7 {Wins a pawn, but not the game, as Black gets an attack.} Rxb2 20. Bxc4 (20. Rxh7 $4 {is too greedy, as Black wins after} Nb3 21. Rxc4 Rxa3 {When Ra1 + is an unstoppable threat.}) 20... Kf6 21. Rxh7 Nxc4 22. Rxc4 Rxa3 {Black is about to put both rooks on the second rank and cause trouble for White.} 23. Kf1 {White had to run away from the checkmate, but as a result, there's no way to defend the f2 -pawn.} Raa2 {Black is winning back the pawns.} *

