e shots.}) 12... Ne5 {The indirect threat on g2 forces the bishop back.} 13. Bf1 Qh4+ {This is the right time for this check, when White doesn't have Kf1 .} 14. g3 Nxg3 15. Qf2 {White can't give up the rook in the current circumstances, but then Black gets a much-improved version of a familiar endgame (the 10... Qf6 line.)} Nf5 16. Qxh4 Nxh4 17. Kf2 f6 {The threats on the f3 -pawn makes White's development very difficult, and there's no chasing the knights away.} *

