ard. Black can get an equal game.} Rad8 {I think this is an accurate moveorder. Black gets ready to push d4 in the future.} 14. Rb1 {White tries to punish Black for delaying the recapture of the c5 -pawn, but we have some resources in the position too.} Ne5 {It turns out putting the queen and rook on the same diagonal was not the best idea.} ({Don't fall for} 14... Nxd2 $2 {when White has} 15. b4 {getting everything protected with an advantage.}) 15. b4 Nxd3+ 16. Qxd3 Qc7 {Having the rook and queen on the same diagonal as Black's bishop will cost White material. It's time for a bail-out.} 17. Bb2 Nxd2 18. Qxf5 Nxb1 19. Bxg7 Kxg7 {White sacrifices everything and gets the draw by perpetual via Qf6 and Qg5.} *

