ets stuck in the center.} (13. Bd2 $4 {is simply a blunder. Black wins after} Nxd2 14. Nxd2 (14. Bxf5 Nxf3+ {Nasty double-check.}) (14. Qxd2 Bxd3 {exploits the pin.}) 14... Nb4 {when White is forced to give up the exchange under very bad circumstances.} 15. axb4 Qxa1+ 16. Qb1 Qxb1+ 17. Bxb1 Bxb1 18. Nxb1 a5 {There's no way of keeping the queenside pawns defended and Black will win with the extra rook.}) 13... b6 {An excellent response for Black. We need to get the rooks involved pronto.} 14. Nh4 {Starts an operation to force Black's pieces back.} Be6 15. f3 {It turns out we don't need to retreat the knight.} bxc5 16. fxe4 c4 {When we're winning back the piece and White's king is not happy about the circumstances.} 17. Bxc4 dxc4 {The engines think Black is winning!} *

