aven't developed any pieces.} Bxe4 17. Qf4 O-O {A great counter-sacrifice! White's king is still in trouble.} 18. Nxe4 {Snacking on Black's bishop lets Black's pieces come to life.} Rae8 ({Avoid} 18... Rfe8 $4 19. f3 f5 20. Bc4+ Kh8 21. O-O-O fxe4 22. Bf7 {when it turns out there was a reason we needed the rook on the f-file.}) 19. f3 f5 {Black will regain the piece and get both rooks involved at the same time. It may be about equal, but I would definitely prefer Black.} *

