aven't developed any pieces.} Bxe4 17. Qf4 O-O {A great counter-sacrifice! White's king is still in trouble.} 18. h5 {Doesn't win anything for White.} Qh6 {There's a counter-pin on White's queen.} 19. O-O-O Bd5 20. Bd3 Rae8 {Leads to a fascinating struggle, where both the h7 -pawn and the c5 -pawn are in trouble. The engines say it's equal, but either player could win here.} *

