 files to control. White has a winning advantage despite having given up two rooks for a queen (and a pawn).}) 14. b4 {This is one of White's most exciting tries. White offers the rook in the corner, but it's a trap!} Bxf3 ({Just as in the 13...Rac8 line, taking the present is not a good idea. The queen is trapped after} 14... Qxa1 $2 15. Bb2 Qa2 16. Ra1 Qxa1+ 17. Bxa1 {White's pawns work harmoniously together and the rooks don't have any open files to control. White has a winning advantage despite having given up two rooks for a queen and a pawn.}) 15. gxf3 {Is a big blunder.} Qg6+ 16. Kh1 Nxf2+ {When there's a double attack on White's king and queen.} 17. Rxf2 Qxc2 *

