1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d5 5. cxd5 Qxd5 {Black immediately starts the counter-attack! Normally we wouldn't bring the queen out this early, but White did it, so why not? Our justification is putting pressure on the undefended d4 -pawn.} 6. Nf3 Qf5 7. Qb3 {Avoiding the queen trade is by far White's most challenging option.} Nc6 ({The bishop needed protection, and unfortunately the strategically preferable} 7... c5 $6 {to include the c-pawn in the fight for the center is well met by} 8. a3 Ba5 9. Qc4 {when White gets a serious advantage due to the undefended bishop on c8 .}) 8. Bd2 O-O 9. e3 Bd6 {The combination of e3 and Bd2 make White well-placed to deal with the immediate e5 -pawn break, so we're in need of a prepatory move to facilitate it.} 10. Nb5 {This is the only way to cause some problems for Black's e5 -plan.} e5 {It turns out the threat against the bishop doesn't prevent us from striking in the center.} 11. dxe5 Bxe5 {This time we don't want to allow Nxd6 . If White want the bishop, they will have to give away the important defensive knight on f3 .} 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. f4 (13. Nxc7 $4 {runs into} Ne4 {when the threat to f2 causes White's position to collapse.} 14. f3 $2 Nxf3+ $1 {A display of force secures Black a winning attack.} 15. gxf3 Qxf3) 13... Nc6 14. Nxc7 Rb8 {Black has given up a pawn, but in return White's king is looking poorly protected.} 15. Be2 {This very natural developing move is a mistake, which illustrates the serious trouble White faces.} Rd8 {Targeting the d2 -bishop delays White's castling.} 16. Rd1 Qe4 {A very clever move, preparing Qe7 .} 17. O-O Qe7 {White got the king to safety, but in the meantime we found a new target: the knight on c7 .} 18. Nb5 a6 19. Na3 {The Qe7 -plan was brilliant because it forces the knight out on the rim, where it most certainly is dim.} (19. Nc3 $4 {loses to} Rxd2 20. Rxd2 Qxe3+ {when Black will emerge from the tactics a piece up.}) 19... Be6 20. Qc2 Rbc8 {All Black's pieces make sense, and in many lines, we'll win back the pawn we're down by surprisingly capturing on a2 .} *

