knight landing on c4 has gotten the a3 -pawn in trouble once again.} 26. Bc1 f5 {Black is being aggressive on both flanks.} 27. gxf5 exf5 {The position is extremely difficult for both sides. White has been forced on the defensive, but has a pawn up, the bishop pair and more pawns in the center. On the other hand black can try to take advantage of White's queen completely out of play in the corner, and the lack of pawn shelter in front of White's king. The engines say it's equal -- 0.00 -- but in reality, this is anyone's game.} *

