term square for the queen.} 14. Qc4 {This is the only square where the queen keeps the c3 -bishop defended, taking the sting out of Black's usual Ne4 -response. But the queen is exposed, and Black gets interesting play...} Be6 {Getting the pieces out while attacking the opponent's queen.} 15. Qd3 Qxd3 {Black has to exchange queens, which straightens out white's pawn structure and goes into an endgame down a pawn. Even so black has good counter chances.} 16. exd3 Nd5 {The knight has a fantastic position on d5 . Black has great control of the light squares and will create good pressure on the f-file. Black's plan involves Rae8 and f5 to exploit the superior activity of Black's pieces.} *

